dynamicportals.command.bread.id: A portal with the id %s has been created
dynamicportals.command.bread.help:
§6[DynamicPortals]§r
The dynamic portals command is similar to the execute command, having multiple different arguments which can be filled in in any order.

These arguments are as follows:
§aFormat: §e[Required/Optional, Type, Name]§r
  §6[Req, Vec2, size]§r Size: two decimal numbers representing how large the portal should be.
  §6[Opt, Vec3, position]§r Position: the position of the portal.
  §6[Opt, Vec3, rotation]§r Rotation: which direction the portal should be facing. This includes pitch, yaw, and roll.
  §6[Opt, Vec3, normal]§r Normal: \"normal\" vector of the portal. This is used for deciding which direction the portal should be rendered from.
  §6[Opt, Text, type]§r Type: the type of the portal. By default, the options are: basic, which is a portal with no overlay, nether, and end.
  §6[Opt, Bool, frontonly]§r Front Only: whether or not the back side should be able to render/

§6[Examples]§r
§a/dynamicportals size 5 5 create §rcreates a portal with a width and height of 5, at the player's (or executor's) feet, and rotated the way the player is facing.
dynamicportals.command.bread.mirror: A portal has been created with the id %s. It is currently a mirror, but can be turned into a portal by creating another one which targets it.
dynamicportals.command.bread.target: A portal has been created with UUID %s and added to the net with UUID %s.
dynamicportals.command.cheese.size_crab: I'm not sure why you're seeing this, so report what exactly your command was to https://github.com/GiantLuigi4/dynamicportals/issues
dynamicportals.command.cheese.missing_ar: In order to create a portal, you must supply the following arguments: [size:Vec2]
dynamicportals.command.cheese.modify_mis: In order to modify a portal, you must supply the at least an option before the modify keyword (target, size, etc.)
dynamicportals.command.cheese.missing_si: In order to create a portal, you must supply an argument for the size of the portal.
dynamicportals.command.cheese.invalid_ta: Didn't find any portal for the specified target. The portal will be a mirror.
